@node How2Play

                            Mozaika

  The aim of the game is by exchanging the figures on the board, to
arrange them, so they can fit together. For the arrangement, the player
have given a fixed amount of time. The game features four game modes:
Nine/Sixteen figures and Easy/Hard.

Good Luck.

In the title screen there are four choices:

Game         - For a new game.

Instructions - Shows short page of instructions.

Hall of Fame - Shows the best puzzlers.

Exit to OS   - Quits the game.

The parts are selectable with clicking the mouse over the appropriate
text, pressing on the keyboard of 1, 2, 3 or 4, or from the menu.

In the Title screen there is a possibility for changing the game settings:
the number of the figures, which need to be arranged - @{b}Nine@{ub} or @{b}Sixteen@{ub},
and the mode of the game - @{b}Easy@{ub} or @{b}Hard@{ub}. These are selectable from the
second menu.


During the game:

Press on the keyboard:

'@{b}Escape@{ub}' - To quit the current game.
'@{b}F10@{ub}'    - To begin new game.

'@{b}A@{ub}'-'@{b}P@{ub}'  - To select a figure labeled with a letter,
or use the mouse to exchange the figures.

